# CADEX OPEN_LOOPS.log — unresolved issues, pending decisions, risky assumptions
# This file prevents token-heavy re-discovery. If something is unresolved,
# write it here so the next session loads it instead of finding it again.
#
# STATUS values:
#   open      — not yet resolved, actively blocking or pending
#   watching  — not blocking now, but needs monitoring
#   resolved  — closed (keep for 2 weeks, then archive)
#
# TYPE values:
#   bug       — known defect not yet fixed
#   decision  — choice that needs to be made
#   assumption — working assumption that needs verification
#   blocker   — external dependency blocking progress
#   debt      — technical debt to address later

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SCHEMA — copy this block for each new open loop
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ---
# id:          OL-[NNN]
# type:        bug | decision | assumption | blocker | debt
# status:      open | watching | resolved
# title:       [one line description]
# detail:      [what is unknown, what was tried, what is at risk]
# affects:     [file, feature, or system area]
# opened:      YYYY-MM-DD
# resolved:    YYYY-MM-DD | null
# resolution:  [how it was resolved, if resolved]
# ---

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EXAMPLE ENTRIES (delete and replace with your own)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

